import mysql.connector

conn = mysql.connector.connect(
    host="localhost",
    user="root",
    password="your_password",
    database="your_database"
)

ðŸŒ€ Restart MySQL manually each time WSL is restarted:

sudo service mysql start

You can create a shortcut/alias in your ~/.bashrc:

alias mysqlon='sudo service mysql start'

Then simply run:

mysqlon



ðŸŒ€  Bonus: Create and connect to a test database
sudo mysql -u root -p

Inside the MySQL shell:

CREATE DATABASE testdb;
CREATE USER 'luispastrana'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'P@5tr4n4L3mu5';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON testdb.* TO 'luispastrana'@'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
exit;


Then connect from Python:

conn = mysql.connector.connect(
    host="localhost",
    user="luispastrana",
    password="P@5tr4n4L3mu5",
    database="testdb"
)
